---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero2 from '~/components/widgets/Hero2.astro';
import CallToAction from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';
import FAQs from '~/components/widgets/FAQs.astro';
import Button from '~/components/ui/Button.astro';
import Image from '~/components/common/Image.astro';
import Features from '~/components/widgets/Features.astro';
import AboutSection from '~/components/widgets/AboutSection.astro';
import Steps from '~/components/widgets/Steps.astro';
import Features2 from '~/components/widgets/Features2.astro';

const appStoreImg = '~/assets/images/app-store-disabled.png';
const appStoreDownloadLink = 'https://github.com/onwidget/astrowind';

const googlePlayImg = '~/assets/images/google-play-disabled.png';
const googlePlayDownloadLink = 'https://github.com/onwidget/astrowind';

const metadata = {
  title: 'You Know You App Homepage',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Hero2 Widget ******************* -->

  <Hero2
    image={{
      src: '~/assets/images/hero-image.png',
      alt: 'You Kno You Hero Image',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="title">
      <span class="text-accent dark:text-white highlight">Track Your Symptoms</span>
      <br /> Take Control of Your Health
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <span class="hidden sm:inline">
        With You Know You, easily track your symptoms and monitor them over time. Log a new symptom event with a single
        tap and gain insights into your health with daily timelines and monthly heatmaps. Designed to empower you and
        those you care about with clear, visual data to better understand your health.
      </span>
    </Fragment>

    <div slot="actions" class="flex max-w-sm gap-4">
      <Button variant="link" href={appStoreDownloadLink}>
        <Image src={appStoreImg} alt="App Store Image" width={200} />
      </Button>

      <Button variant="link" href={googlePlayDownloadLink}>
        <Image src={googlePlayImg} alt="Google Play Image" width={200} />
      </Button>
    </div>
  </Hero2>

  <!-- Features Widget *************** -->

  <Features
    id="features"
    title="Features"
    items={[
      {
        title: 'One Tap Tracking',
        description:
          'Quickly record a new symptom event with just one tap, making it simple to track your health in real-time.',
        icon: 'tabler:hand-click',
      },
      {
        title: 'Timeline',
        description:
          'Effortlessly review your symptoms over the day with a clear and concise timeline, giving you instant insights into your health patterns.',
        icon: 'tabler:clock-hour-4',
      },
      {
        title: 'Heat Map',
        description:
          'Visualize your symptoms over longer periods with a heatmap, allowing you to identify trends and patterns at a glance.',
        icon: 'tabler:flame',
      },
      {
        title: 'Customize Symtoms',
        description:
          'Easily customize the colors and names of symptoms to suit your preferences, making your health data uniquely yours.',
        icon: 'tabler:palette',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <AboutSection
    actions={[
      {
        variant: 'primary',
        text: 'Get Early Access Now',
        href: '#',
        target: '_blank',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: '~/assets/images/spreadsheets.png',
      alt: 'image of spreadsheet that is filled with complex and confusing data ',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="title"
      >Why We Made <span class="text-accent dark:text-white highlight">You Know You</span>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <span class="block text-left">
        You Know You was born out of a personal journey filled with frustration and uncertainty. My wife and I were
        struggling with mysterious symptoms that seemed to have no clear cause. In an attempt to find answers, we
        resorted to tracking every detail—she in a large, chaotic Excel spreadsheet, and I in a paper journal and
        various apps like Notes. But none of these methods could show us how our symptoms were appearing and evolving
        over time. Instead, they only added to our frustration, making it difficult to see the full picture of our
        health.
        <br /><br />
        After spending thousands on medical bills and testing that provided no clear answers, we realized we needed a better
        way to monitor our health. We suspected it was food-related, but without clear data, it was impossible to know for
        sure. We found ourselves making multiple visits to different doctors, each of whom would tell us to try one test
        or track only one symptom, only to return and repeat the process without real progress.
        <br /><br />
        That’s why we created You Know You. Our mission is simple: to help people identify their symptoms without the need
        for excessive medical expenses. By giving users the tools to track and visualize their symptoms over time, You Know
        You doesn’t replace the expertise of doctors, but it does empower patients to better inform their healthcare providers.
        With clear, visual data, users can work more effectively with their doctors to diagnose underlying issues faster
        and more cost-effectively, reducing the need for multiple visits and extensive testing.
        <br /><br />
        Whether you’re dealing with unexplained symptoms like we were, or you’re just looking to keep a closer eye on your
        health, You Know You is designed to empower you with the insights you need to take control of your well-being.
      </span>
    </Fragment>
  </AboutSection>

  <!-- Steps Widget ****************** -->

  <Steps
    title="How It Works"
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Step 1: <span class="font-medium">Create a New Symptom Event</span>',
        description:
          'Start by creating a new symptom event to track. Simply name your symptom and choose a color to represent it.',
        icon: 'tabler:plus',
      },
      {
        title: 'Step 2: <span class="font-medium">Log an Event with One Tap</span>',
        description:
          'Visualize your symptoms over longer periods with a heatmap, allowing you to identify trends and patterns at a glance.',
        icon: 'tabler:hand-click',
      },
      {
        title: 'Step 3: <span class="font-medium">Review Your Timeline</span>',
        description:
          'Dive into the details with the timeline view, where you can see each symptom hour by hour, giving you a clear picture of your day.',
        icon: 'tabler:clock-hour-4',
      },
      {
        title: 'Step 4: <span class="font-medium">Identify Patterns with the Heatmap</span>',
        description:
          'Navigate through the calendar to find ‘hotspots’ using the heat map view. See how your symptoms have appeared over the month, making it easier to spot trends.',
        icon: 'tabler:flame',
      },
      {
        title: 'Step 5: <span class="font-medium">Customize Your Symptoms</span>',
        description:
          'Easily edit the name and color of your symptoms by long pressing on the symptom tile. Personalize your tracking to suit your needs.',
        icon: 'tabler:palette',
      },
      {
        title: 'Step 6: <span class="font-medium">Once Healed Remove Symptoms</span>',
        description:
          "Once you've overcome a symptom, long press the symptom tile to open the details and delete it. Keep your tracking focused and relevant.",
        icon: 'tabler:check',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: '~/assets/images/Woman Holding Iphone Mockup copy.webp',
      alt: 'Woman holding a phone looking at the You Know You app journal screen',
    }}
  />

